fields.description:
If you don't have subtasks enabled in the instance and you create a custom issue type with the same name("Sub-task") when you try to enable the sub-tasks in "Jira Admin > Issues > Sub-tasks" you get a 500 error because Jira tries to create the issue type with the same name.
{noformat}
Referer URL: http://localhost:8080/secure/admin/subtasks/ManageSubTasks.jspa

com.atlassian.jira.exception.CreateException: Issue Type with name 'Sub-task' already exists.

{noformat}
The suggestion is to add a more friendly message in the UI telling the customer to remove the already existing issue type. Since Jira throws a 500 error it's some time misleading.
